---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import EndorsementForm from "../components/EndorsementForm.tsx";
import "../styles/base.css";
---

<Layout
  title="Endorsements | Tech for Palestine"
  description="Request an endorsement from Tech for Palestine for your campaign or organization. Learn what we look for and how the review process works."
>
  <main>
    <div class="relative isolate">
      <svg
        class="absolute inset-x-0 top-0 -z-10 h-[64rem] w-full stroke-gray-200 [mask-image:radial-gradient(32rem_32rem_at_center,white,transparent)]"
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
        <defs>
          <pattern
            id="endorsements-pattern"
            width="200"
            height="200"
            x="50%"
            y="-1"
            patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse"
          >
            <path d="M.5 200V.5H200" fill="none"></path>
          </pattern>
        </defs>
        <rect width="100%" height="100%" stroke-width="0" fill="url(#endorsements-pattern)"></rect>
      </svg>

      <div class="px-6 py-24 sm:py-32 lg:px-8">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
          <!-- Page Header -->
          <div class="mb-16 text-center">
            <p class="text-base font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-700">
              Tech for Palestine
            </p>
            <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-5xl">
              Endorsement Requests
            </h1>
            <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-8 text-gray-600">
              T4P endorsements signal to the broader tech and Palestine advocacy community that your
              campaign aligns with our values and goals. Here's what you need to know before
              applying.
            </p>
            <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-2xl text-sm text-gray-500">
              Note: We don't fully vet every endorsement. Our review is based on available
              information and community knowledge, not exhaustive due diligence.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- What we look for -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">What we look for</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
              <div class="rounded-lg border border-green-100 bg-green-50 p-6">
                <div class="mb-3 inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-green-100">
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="h-5 w-5 text-green-700">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3.75 13.5l10.5-11.25L12 10.5h8.25L9.75 21.75 12 13.5H3.75z" />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="mb-2 font-semibold text-green-900">Will it be impactful?</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-green-800/70">
                  We look for campaigns and initiatives with meaningful potential to advance
                  Palestinian rights or hold tech companies accountable.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-lg border border-blue-100 bg-blue-50 p-6">
                <div class="mb-3 inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-blue-100">
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="h-5 w-5 text-blue-700">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 17.25v1.007a3 3 0 01-.879 2.122L7.5 21h9l-.621-.621A3 3 0 0115 18.257V17.25m6-12V15a2.25 2.25 0 01-2.25 2.25H5.25A2.25 2.25 0 013 15V5.25m18 0A2.25 2.25 0 0018.75 3H5.25A2.25 2.25 0 003 5.25m18 0H3" />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="mb-2 font-semibold text-blue-900">Does it relate to tech?</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-blue-800/70">
                  Our endorsements carry the most weight in the tech industry, and we prioritize
                  campaigns where that community connection matters.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-lg border border-purple-100 bg-purple-50 p-6">
                <div class="mb-3 inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-purple-100">
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="h-5 w-5 text-purple-700">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15 19.128a9.38 9.38 0 002.625.372 9.337 9.337 0 004.121-.952 4.125 4.125 0 00-7.533-2.493M15 19.128v-.003c0-1.113-.285-2.16-.786-3.07M15 19.128v.106A12.318 12.318 0 018.624 21c-2.331 0-4.512-.645-6.374-1.766l-.001-.109a6.375 6.375 0 0111.964-3.07M12 6.375a3.375 3.375 0 11-6.75 0 3.375 3.375 0 016.75 0zm8.25 2.25a2.625 2.625 0 11-5.25 0 2.625 2.625 0 015.25 0z" />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="mb-2 font-semibold text-purple-900">Do we know the people involved?</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-purple-800/70">
                  It helps if someone from T4P can speak to the initiative. New organizations are
                  welcome. A personal connection goes a long way.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- FAQ -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Frequently asked questions</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <details class="group rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white">
                <summary
                  class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-6 font-semibold text-gray-900"
                >
                  What does a T4P endorsement mean?
                  <svg
                    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                  >
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
                  </svg>
                </summary>
                <p class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  A T4P endorsement is a public statement of support for a specific campaign or
                  initiative. It signals to our community of thousands of tech workers that the
                  campaign aligns with our values. It does not imply financial support or ongoing
                  partnership.
                </p>
              </details>

              <details class="group rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white">
                <summary
                  class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-6 font-semibold text-gray-900"
                >
                  How long does the review process take?
                  <svg
                    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                  >
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
                  </svg>
                </summary>
                <p class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  We aim to review all requests within 3–5 days. We'll reach out if we need
                  additional information.
                </p>
              </details>

              <details class="group rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white">
                <summary
                  class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-6 font-semibold text-gray-900"
                >
                  Can T4P projects apply for endorsements?
                  <svg
                    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                  >
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
                  </svg>
                </summary>
                <p class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  Yes. If you're already a T4P incubator project and are launching a specific
                  campaign, you can request an endorsement. Check the "T4P project" box in the form
                  and our review will reflect that context.
                </p>
              </details>

              <details class="group rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white">
                <summary
                  class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-6 font-semibold text-gray-900"
                >
                  What happens if our request is declined?
                  <svg
                    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                  >
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
                  </svg>
                </summary>
                <p class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  We'll let you know and, where possible, share the reason. Declinations are not
                  permanent. If your campaign evolves or new information is available, you're
                  welcome to reapply.
                </p>
              </details>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Form -->
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-8">
            <h2 class="mb-2 text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Submit a request</h2>
            <p class="mb-8 text-gray-600">
              Fill out the form below and our team will be in touch.
            </p>
            <EndorsementForm client:only="react" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
